---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Rows describing exactly what the site measures. Rendered as a table below.
const collected = [
  { data: 'Page views', detail: 'Which pages are opened and in what order, as aggregate counts.' },
  { data: 'Referrer', detail: 'The site or link that sent you here (for example a search engine or a post).' },
  { data: 'Approximate region', detail: 'Country or region, derived at request time. Your IP address is never stored.' },
  { data: 'Device basics', detail: 'Browser, operating system, and screen size bucket, so the layout can be tested where it matters.' },
  { data: 'Clicks on key buttons', detail: 'Anonymous counts of actions like "Star on GitHub" or "Read the docs". No text you type is collected.' },
];
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy · Gaia"
  description="What the gaia-agent.com website measures: cookieless, aggregate analytics with no personal data, no tracking cookies, and no consent banner needed."
  active="privacy"
>

<style is:global>
  .pv-table { width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:.92rem; }
  .pv-table th {
    font-family:'Cinzel',serif; font-size:.66rem; letter-spacing:.18em; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--ink-soft); text-align:left; border-bottom:2px solid var(--rule); padding:.8rem 1rem;
  }
  .pv-table td { border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); padding:1rem; color:var(--ink-soft); vertical-align:top; line-height:1.6; }
  .pv-table td:first-child { color:var(--ink); font-weight:600; white-space:nowrap; }
  .pv-pill {
    display:inline-flex; align-items:center; border:1px solid var(--rule);
    padding:.28rem .55rem; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; font-size:.68rem;
    color:var(--ink-soft); background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--bg) 70%, transparent);
  }
  .pv-card {
    border:1px solid var(--moss); background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--moss) 7%, var(--surface));
    padding:1.6rem 1.5rem;
  }
</style>

<main class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-28">
  <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
  <h1 class="display mt-4 text-5xl md:text-6xl leading-[1.02] tracking-tight max-w-3xl">
    We count visits, not people.
  </h1>
  <p class="muted text-[16px] mt-6 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
    This is the privacy notice for the <strong style="color:var(--ink);">gaia-agent.com website</strong>, not the Gaia agent you run yourself.
    The site uses privacy-first, cookieless analytics so we can see what is useful and what is broken, without building a profile of you.
  </p>
  <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
    <span class="pv-pill">no cookies</span>
    <span class="pv-pill">no personal data</span>
    <span class="pv-pill">no consent banner needed</span>
    <span class="pv-pill">open-source tooling</span>
  </div>

  <hr class="hr-script mt-16 mb-14" />

  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">What we measure</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="pv-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data</th>
            <th>What it is</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {collected.map((row) => (
            <tr>
              <td>{row.data}</td>
              <td>{row.detail}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="muted text-sm mt-6 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      Everything above is aggregate. There is no cross-site tracking, no advertising network, no fingerprinting, and nothing that identifies you as an individual.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="hr-script mt-16 mb-14" />

  <section class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
    <div class="md:col-span-4">
      <p class="eyebrow">The tool</p>
      <h2 class="display text-3xl md:text-4xl mt-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">Umami, by design.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="md:col-span-8">
      <p class="muted leading-relaxed">
        Analytics run through <a href="https://umami.is" target="_blank" style="color:var(--moss);">Umami</a>, an open-source, privacy-focused analytics tool.
        It does not use cookies and does not collect personal data, which is why you did not have to click through a consent banner to read this site.
      </p>
      <p class="muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
        The script only loads on the live site. It is a single lightweight file and does not follow you anywhere else.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hr-script mt-16 mb-14" />

  <section>
    <div class="pv-card">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Why there is no cookie banner</p>
      <p class="muted leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Consent banners exist because most analytics store cookies and personal data.
        This site does neither, so under GDPR and ePrivacy rules there is nothing to consent to.
        We would rather show you the site than a pop-up.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hr-script mt-16 mb-14" />

  <section>
    <h2 class="display text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight">Questions</h2>
    <p class="muted mt-4 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
      Gaia is open source and this site is too. If something here is unclear, or you want a measurement removed, open an issue on the repository.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="https://github.com/sho0pi/gaia" target="_blank" data-umami-event="open-github" class="btn btn-primary">Open GitHub ↗</a>
      <a href="/security/" class="btn btn-ghost">Security model</a>
    </div>
    <p class="muted text-xs mt-8 mono">Website analytics only. The Gaia agent you self-host keeps its own data on your machine - see the <a href="/security/" style="color:var(--moss);">security page</a>.</p>
  </section>
</main>

</Layout>
